    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Power Cylinders - Installation - Piston
        Cooling Tubes
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="1">
        <title>Piston Cooling Tubes</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>You may need to rotate crankshaft in order to gain access to some piston cooling tubes.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650827" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh06/H06091.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the piston cooling tube</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston cooling tube</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To avoid engine damage, the piston cooling tubes use a special patch type mounting bolt to prevent
                    loosening. Do not substitute.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The bolt-on piston cooling tubes are self aligning.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place piston cooling tubes onto crankcase mounting pad.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">When installing the piston cooling tube bolts (M6 x 16), do either of the following:</para>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Install brand
                        <emph type="bold">new</emph>
                        piston cooling tube mounting bolts (patch type), or
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove oil residue and apply Loctite&#174; #242 to the threads of existing piston cooling tube
                        mounting bolts (patch type).
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten each piston cooling tube mounting bolt to the
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_S265APPB01.xml" xrefid="S265APPB01" appearance="hottext">standard torque
                    value</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
